Morocco is set to host the continental football tournament from July 2-23, 2022. The tournament also doubles as the African qualifiers to the 2023 Federation Internationale de Football Association Women's World Cup, with only four teams set to represent Africa at the global spectacle in Australia and New Zealand. The final draw for the AWCON will be held on a date to be announced. Focusing on the upcoming tournament, Mosibudi Makhura spoke to Samuel Ahmadu, listen further. --Rachel Makhura/ ChannelAfrica--